Create Template Standard Values
----field----
field: {00E1D306-96BD-4B32-85B4-CD63C53CC6C1}
name: Abstract
key: abstract
content-length: 198

<p>Template Standard Values are important to provide default values, presentation, and insert options. In this article we will learn how to assign Template Standard Values to our Data Templates.</p>
----field----
field: {5A5684BB-8B54-44F6-ABCC-2BADA05ADA5D}
name: Body
key: body
content-length: 4762

<h2 style="text-align: left;">About Template Standard Values</h2>
<p style="text-align: left;">For a given data template, developers often want to create default values. <strong>Template Standard Values</strong> (TSV) define not only default values, but also default settings. In Sitecore, this construct serves as a way to define both default values and default settings for a given data template.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">For example, if we want to provide default values in a rich text field called <strong>Description</strong>, we could use the <strong>Template Standard Values</strong> to set the default field value to "Place your description here...".  That way, everytime a new item is created based on this data template, the field will come already populated with this value, indicating to business users where to place their text.  Similarly, we change default settings on the data template such as Workflow by setting it on the Template Standard Values.  This way, everytime an item is created based on this data template, the item is immediately placed into the appropriate Workflow.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: left;">What are Tokens?</h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">What happens if we want to set default values that tend to change when each item is created such as item name or created date.  This is where <strong>Tokens</strong> come in.  We can use tokens like $name and $date to show the item name and the item created date respectively.  To use a token, just place them in any text field on the Template Standard Values.  Other tokens include $id, $time and $now.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: left;">What are Insert Options?</h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">Imagine that your website has two site sections: a Products section featuring Product Descriptions and a News section with News Articles.  Using <strong>Insert Options</strong>, Sitecore Developers define what types of content Business Users can create and where they can create it in the Content Tree. In other words, <strong>Insert Options</strong> let Developers mandate where and what Business Users can create.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">For the Product section, a Developer assigns the Product Description data template as the single <strong>Insert Option</strong>. For the News section, a Developer assigns the News Article data template as the single <strong>Insert Option</strong>. In this manner, Business Users can only create items of the type Product Description in the Products section and only items of the type News Article in the News section.</p>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Template Standard Values Activity</h2>
<ol>
  <li>
  <div style="text-align: left;">We'll start by creating Template Standard Values for our Home Template.  Select the Home Template ("/Templates/MyFirstSite/Home").  With the Builder tab selected, select the Options tab from the ribbon, then select <strong>Standard Values</strong>.  Your <strong>_Standard Values</strong> item with then be created as a child item.  <br />
  <br />
  <img style="width: 594px; height: 316px;border: #000000 1px solid;" alt="Screenshot 1" src="~/media/77B3636612B44AA2A4A8E1E65DFA4806.ashx" /><br />
  <br />
  </div>
  </li>
  <li>
  <p style="text-align: left;"> Now that we have a <strong>_Standard Values</strong> item, we can start editing it.  Select the <strong>_Standard Values</strong> item and input "$name" into the <strong>Title</strong> field and some default text of your choosing into the <strong>Description</strong> field. <br />
  <br />
  <img style="width: 584px; height: 376px;border: #000000 1px solid;" alt="Screenshot 2" src="~/media/5574271DE7FD43A3A5A800A9978E7AC7.ashx" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
  <p style="text-align: left;">Let's repeat steps 1 and 2 for our Product Template ("/Templates/MyFirstSite/Product").</p>
  </li>
  <li>
  <p style="text-align: left;">Now let's set Insert Options on our <strong>My First Site Exercise</strong> item.  Select the <strong>My First Site Exercise</strong> item, select the <strong>Configure</strong> tab in the ribbon and click <strong>Assign</strong>.  When the dialog appears, remove Standard Fields and add your Product template.  Remember we would typically assign <strong>Insert Options</strong> on the <strong>Template Standard Values</strong> but since this site only has two levels, it isn't necessary.  <br />
  <br />
  <img style="width: 592px; height: 279px;border: #000000 1px solid;" alt="Screenshot 3" src="~/media/2D5567C4FF5F44F5A9D25916BE1422B2.ashx" /><br />
  <br />
  <img width="480" height="298" style="width: 470px; height: 297px;border: #000000 1px solid;" alt="Screenshot 4" src="~/media/CAE8386AA4AA4F13B0C8342A3327ACA1.ashx" /><br />
  <br />
  </p>
  </li>
</ol>
